## Key Programming Concepts Learned

- Variables store values
- Data types define what a variable can hold
- Java is statically typed
- Integer division behaves differently from decimal division
- Comparisons return booleans
- Programs make decisions using conditional statements
- Logical operators combine multiple conditions
- Loops eliminate repetitive code
- Arrays store collections of related values
- Professional Java code avoids hardcoded values whenever possible

